# API Patterns

## REST Conventions
- Use plural nouns for resource endpoints
- GET /users - list, GET /users/:id - get one
- POST /users - create, PUT /users/:id - update
- DELETE /users/:id - remove

## Error Responses
- Always return { error: string, code: number }
- Use HTTP status codes correctly
- Log errors server-side, never expose stack traces
